Purpose   : Final pre-Flutter bootstrap readiness audit


1. SUMMARY
----------
The repository is structurally well-formed and contains a complete Node.js-based
developer toolchain (commitlint, husky, semantic-release), three CI workflows
(commitlint, flutter, release), Flutter SDK version pinning via FVM (.fvmrc), and
comprehensive documentation (README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md). The latest automated
release is v1.7.0 (2026-03-10).

However, three active issues prevent the repository from being considered fully
green. The most critical is that all three CI workflows currently fail on `main`
because the `egohygiene/ai` Git submodule repository is not accessible — the
remote reports "Repository not found". Until that submodule can be cloned
successfully, the Release and Flutter workflows cannot complete. In addition, a
non-conventional commit on this PR branch causes the commitlint workflow to fail.
Finally, five high-severity npm dependency vulnerabilities are present.

Overall readiness status: CONDITIONAL — toolchain and documentation are sound;
three issues must be addressed before the repository can be declared fully green.


