3. FINDINGS
-----------

FINDING-01 [CRITICAL] — ai submodule repository not found
  All three CI workflows (commitlint, flutter, release) fail on the main branch.
  The `egohygiene/ai` submodule is registered at:
    git@github.com:egohygiene/ai.git
  During CI checkout with `submodules: recursive`, the runner rewrites the SSH URL
  to HTTPS and attempts to clone it. The remote responds with:
    "remote: Repository not found."
  This error occurs in the Flutter and Release jobs (which request `submodules: recursive`)
  and prevents those workflows from completing. Root causes may include:
    a) The egohygiene/ai repository is private and the AI_DEPLOY_KEY secret is not
       provisioned, expired, or incorrectly scoped.
    b) The egohygiene/ai repository does not yet exist.
    c) The AI_DEPLOY_KEY secret is present but the corresponding deploy key has been
       revoked or was not added to the egohygiene/ai repository with read access.
  Impact: Release automation and Flutter CI are broken on main until resolved.

FINDING-02 [ACTIVE] — Non-conventional commit on this PR branch
  The first commit on branch `copilot/final-audit-repository-readiness` has the
  message "Initial plan", which does not follow the Conventional Commits format.
  This causes the commitlint CI workflow to fail for this PR with:
    "subject may not be empty [subject-empty]"
    "type may not be empty [type-empty]"
  This finding is self-referential: the audit agent's own initial commit violated
  the convention. The branch may need its history amended or a fixup commit added
  before merging.

FINDING-03 [WARNING] — 5 high-severity npm dependency vulnerabilities
  `npm audit` reports five high-severity vulnerabilities in the installed packages.
  Root cause: tar <=7.5.9 has "Hardlink Path Traversal via Drive-Relative Linkpath"
  (GHSA-qffp-2rhf-9h96). The vulnerable tar version is pulled in transitively by:
    npm → @semantic-release/npm → semantic-release
  A fix is available via `npm audit fix --force`, but it would install
  semantic-release@24.2.9 (a breaking change from the currently configured ^25.x).
  Mitigation: Evaluate whether upgrading to semantic-release@24.2.9 or waiting for
  a semantic-release@25.x patch that bumps tar is the preferred path.

FINDING-04 [WARNING] — Node.js 20 actions deprecation
  The following GitHub Actions run on Node.js 20, which will be deprecated by
  GitHub starting 2 June 2026:
    actions/checkout@v4
    actions/setup-node@v4
    webfactory/ssh-agent@v0.9.1
  CI emits a deprecation warning on every run. After the deprecation date, these
  actions will be forced onto Node.js 24, which may cause unexpected failures.
  Action: Pin each to a newer version tag or SHA that supports Node.js 24 before
  the June 2026 deadline.

FINDING-05 [MINOR] — CHANGELOG.md missing blank line between v1.4.0 and v1.3.0
  The blank separator line between the v1.4.0 and v1.3.0 sections is absent:
    ...# [1.4.0]...\n### Features\n...\n# [1.3.0]...
  This is cosmetic. semantic-release will regenerate the file on the next release,
  so no manual fix is required unless linting is added for CHANGELOG format.


4. SUGGESTED FIXES
------------------

FIX-01 — Resolve ai submodule access (addresses FINDING-01)
  Choose one of the following approaches:
  Option A (Preferred — SSH deploy key):
    1. Verify that the egohygiene/ai repository exists and is accessible.
    2. Generate a new SSH keypair for the deploy key:
         ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "flutter-foundation ci deploy key" -f ai_deploy_key
    3. Add the public key to the egohygiene/ai repository as a read-only deploy key
       (Settings → Deploy keys → Add deploy key, read-only access).
    4. Store the private key as a repository secret in flutter-foundation:
         Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret
         Name: AI_DEPLOY_KEY
    5. Push a trivial commit to main and confirm all three workflows pass.
  Option B (HTTPS submodule — avoids SSH key management):
    1. Update .gitmodules to use the HTTPS URL:
         url = https://github.com/egohygiene/ai.git
    2. If the repository is private, provision a PAT with read:repo scope as a
       repository secret and configure the workflow to pass it via:
         git config --global url."https://<PAT>@github.com/".insteadOf "https://github.com/"

FIX-02 — Amend the non-conventional commit (addresses FINDING-02)
  Before merging this PR, ensure all commits on the branch follow Conventional Commits.
  The "Initial plan" commit should be amended or squashed with a conventional message,
  for example:
    docs(audit): add final pre-Flutter bootstrap readiness audit log

FIX-03 — Address npm audit vulnerabilities (addresses FINDING-03)
  Evaluate upgrading semantic-release or waiting for an upstream fix:
    Option A: Pin semantic-release to a version that ships a non-vulnerable tar.
    Option B: Add a `npm audit --audit-level=critical` gate to CI so only critical
              vulnerabilities block the build (demoting high to non-blocking).

FIX-04 — Update GitHub Actions to Node.js 24-compatible versions (addresses FINDING-04)
  Before June 2026, update each action in the workflows to a tag that supports
  Node.js 24, or set the environment variable on the workflow:
    env:
      FORCE_JAVASCRIPT_ACTIONS_TO_NODE24: true
  Monitor upstream releases of actions/checkout, actions/setup-node, and
  webfactory/ssh-agent for Node.js 24-compatible tags.


